<p>
Generally when one does pottery, you sit first at the Pottery Wheel and then go the Kiln. However, there are a few oddball recipes that forsake clay and just need to be cooked. But an oven won't do (the bakers get upset). And since the forge tends to have too much ore splattered around it, we need the kiln.
</p><br><div align="right">Last Modified By: EQTC Editor Krazick&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

